{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Unsupervised learning discovers hidden structure in data that has no labeled outputs. Instead of learning to predict a correct answer, the model finds patterns, groupings, or compact representations on its own. This paradigm powers embedding models, clustering pipelines, and anomaly detection — all common components in agentic AI systems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "What it is" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In unsupervised learning, the training data contains "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "features only — no labels",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The model must infer structure from the data itself. Common objectives include grouping similar items, reducing dimensionality, or learning a compressed representation that captures the essential information in the input."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Main task categories" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Clustering",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — group data points so that items within a group are more similar to each other than to items in other groups"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dimensionality reduction",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — compress high-dimensional data into fewer dimensions while preserving important structure"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Anomaly detection",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — identify data points that deviate significantly from the learned normal pattern"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Representation learning",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — learn useful feature embeddings that can be reused in downstream tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Why it matters" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Labeled data is expensive to produce at scale. Unsupervised methods let systems learn useful representations from raw, unlabeled corpora — which is exactly how embedding models and LLM pre-training work. An agent's retrieval pipeline depends on embedding models trained with unsupervised or self-supervised objectives to represent documents and queries in a shared vector space."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Clustering and anomaly detection help organize knowledge bases, detect unusual agent behavior, and segment user populations without manual labeling."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Benefits" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No labeling required",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — works on raw data that is abundant and cheap to collect"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Exploratory insight",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — reveals natural groupings and structure that humans may not anticipate"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Transferable representations",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — embeddings learned unsupervised can improve supervised tasks with less labeled data"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Harder to evaluate",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — without ground-truth labels, measuring quality requires indirect metrics or human judgment"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Ambiguous objectives",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — there may be multiple valid clusterings or representations of the same data"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sensitive to hyperparameters",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the number of clusters or components often must be chosen without clear guidance"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "How it works" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Clustering with K-Means" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "K-Means partitions data into "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "k",
            "marks": [{ "type": "code" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " clusters by iteratively assigning each point to the nearest cluster centroid and recomputing centroids until assignments stabilize."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Dimensionality reduction with PCA" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Principal Component Analysis (PCA) finds orthogonal directions of maximum variance in the data and projects inputs onto the top components. This reduces dimensionality while retaining as much information as possible."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Self-supervised learning (a related paradigm)" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-supervised learning generates labels from the data itself. LLM pre-training uses next-token prediction: the model learns to predict each token from preceding context. This is technically unsupervised (no human labels) but creates a supervised-style objective from raw text. Embedding models use contrastive learning — pulling similar pairs closer and pushing dissimilar pairs apart — to learn semantic representations without manual annotation."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Examples" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Clustering customer support tickets by topic without predefined labels:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "python" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from sklearn.datasets import make_blobs\nfrom sklearn.cluster import KMeans\nfrom sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n\nX, _ = make_blobs(n_samples=300, centers=4, random_state=42)\n\nkmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42, n_init=10)\nlabels = kmeans.fit_predict(X)\n\nscore = silhouette_score(X, labels)\nprint(f\"Silhouette score: {score:.3f}\")\nprint(f\"Cluster sizes: {[sum(labels == i) for i in range(4)]}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Reducing dimensionality before visualization or downstream modeling:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": { "language": "python" },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from sklearn.datasets import load_digits\nfrom sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n\nX, y = load_digits(return_X_y=True)\n\npca = PCA(n_components=2)\nX_reduced = pca.fit_transform(X)\n\nprint(f\"Original shape: {X.shape}\")\nprint(f\"Reduced shape: {X_reduced.shape}\")\nprint(f\"Variance explained: {pca.explained_variance_ratio_.sum():.2f}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 3 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Unsupervised learning in agent systems" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Embedding models",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — convert text into vectors for semantic search in RAG pipelines"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Document clustering",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — organize a knowledge base into topic groups without manual tagging"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Anomaly detection",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — flag unusual agent outputs or API call patterns that deviate from normal behavior"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LLM pre-training",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — self-supervised next-token prediction on large text corpora builds the foundation model"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Choosing k arbitrarily",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — the number of clusters should be validated with metrics like silhouette score or the elbow method"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Skipping feature scaling",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — distance-based methods like K-Means are sensitive to feature scale; normalize inputs first"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Treating clusters as ground truth",
                    "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — clusters are model outputs, not objective categories; always validate with domain knowledge"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Best practices" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Standardize or normalize features before applying distance-based algorithms"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use multiple evaluation metrics (silhouette score, Davies-Bouldin index) to compare clusterings"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Inspect cluster contents manually to verify they are semantically meaningful"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prefer pre-trained embedding models over raw text features for semantic clustering tasks"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Mental model" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Unsupervised learning is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sorting a mixed box of items without a predefined catalog",
            "marks": [{ "type": "bold" }]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The algorithm groups items that look alike and separates those that differ, revealing natural categories that may not have been known in advance."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": { "level": 2 },
        "content": [{ "type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Unsupervised learning finds structure in unlabeled data through clustering, dimensionality reduction, or representation learning"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Self-supervised learning (next-token prediction, contrastive learning) is the foundation of LLM and embedding model training"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent retrieval pipelines depend on unsupervised embedding models for semantic search"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Evaluation is indirect — use internal metrics and manual inspection to validate discovered structure"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
